Management Team






Michael N. Thompson Managing Partner and Portfolio Manager
 Mr. Thompson founded BHR Capital LLC in 2009 and is the Portfolio Manager for the investment vehicles managed by BHR Capital LLC.  Mr. Thompson is responsible for all portfolio construction, security selection and risk management activities and oversees BHR’s investment team.  Prior to founding BHR, Mr. Thompson was with Bay Harbour Management, L.C., having joined the firm in 2008 to lead research and investment efforts in the financial and real estate sectors, and to manage the firm’s short investment portfolio.  Mr. Thompson was previously a Managing Director at Wachovia Securities with management responsibilities for a $3+ billion propriety trading book.  Mr. Thompson graduated magna cum laude with a BBA in International Finance from the Honors Program at the University of Georgia where he received Alumni, Governor’s and Hope Scholarships.
  

Michael C. Falk Chief Financial Officer
 Mr. Falk joined BHR Capital LLC in July 2011 as the Chief Accounting Officer.  He was previously with Steel Partners, most recently as the firm's Chief Financial Officer.  Mr. Falk’s other work experience includes K2 Advisors, L.L.C., where he was an accounting manager, and Richard A. Eisner & Co. L.L.P. in the financial services audit group, rising to the position of supervisor.  Mr. Falk received a B.S. in Accounting from Syracuse University and an MBA from Baruch College, City of New York Zicklin Graduate School of Business.  He has been licensed in New York State as a CPA since 1997.
  

 



