Investment Team






Fax Herbert 
 Mr. Herbert joined BHR Capital LLC in May 2013.  Prior to joining the firm, Mr. Herbert was an analyst at Tiger Global Management since January 2011.  Previously, he was an analyst at Venesprie Capital, a Tiger Management seed fund.  Mr. Herbert received a B.A. in Economics from Tufts University, where he oversaw the Tufts Financial Group's student-run investment fund.  Mr. Herbert currently serves as a young alumni advisor to the Tufts Financial Group's board, and has mentored several recent graduates who now work in investment management.  

Nirmal Roy 
 Mr. Roy joined BHR Capital LLC in February 2011.  Prior to joining the firm, Mr. Roy focused on distressed real estate investing at Meadow Partners, a New York based real estate private equity firm.  Previously, Mr. Roy worked in the Principal Finance Group of Silver Point Capital, a hedge fund primarily focused on distressed credit in the public and private sectors.  He began his career at Starwood Capital Group where he focused on the acquisition of real estate assets and public real estate companies in the U.S. and internationally.  Mr. Roy received a Bachelor of Science in Economics, magna cum laude, from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.  

Michael N. Thompson 
 Mr. Thompson is the Portfolio Manager for the investment vehicles managed by BHR Capital, which he founded in 2009.  Mr. Thompson is responsible for all portfolio construction, security selection and risk management activities and oversees BHR’s investment team.  Prior to founding BHR, Mr. Thompson was with Bay Harbour Management, having joined the firm in 2008 to lead research and investment efforts in the financial and real estate sectors, and to manage the firm’s short investment portfolio.  Mr. Thompson was previously a Managing Director at Wachovia Securities with management responsibilities for a $3+ billion proprietary trading book.  Mr. Thompson graduated magna cum laude with a BBA in International Finance from the Honors Program at the University of Georgia where he received Alumni, Governor’s and Hope Scholarships.  

 



